message.content:
I am an AI language model, so I cannot give you a tour of Texas. However, I can provide information about interesting places to visit and activities you may want to do in the state.

1. Visit the Alamo: This historic mission and UNESCO World Heritage site in San Antonio played a crucial role in the Texas Revolution.

2. Walk along the River Walk: Also located in San Antonio, this picturesque network of walkways is lined with shops, restaurants, nightlife venues, and outdoor art installations.

3. Explore Big Bend National Park: The park offers opportunities for hiking, wildlife-watching birding as well as scenic drives through diverse landscapes including mountains and deserts.

4 . Stroll around Austin's 6th Street Entertainment District - Known for its vibrant music scene and many bars & clubs; it's worth spending some time exploring downtown Austin

5 .Explore Space Center Houston - home to NASA's Johnson Space Control & more than 400 space artifacts , exhibits which tell story of America’s human spaceflight program

6 . Visit Amarillo –It has popular attractions like Cadillac Ranch (an art installation consisting of ten partially buried Cadillacs)and Palo Duro Canyon State Park- second largest canyon system in US after Grand Canyon 

7 . Discover Padre Island National Seashore - Home to pristine beaches & important nesting grounds for Kemp’s ridley sea turtles

8 . Marvel at Natural Bridge Caverns near San Antonio– Experience thrilling cave tours or enjoy zipline adventures above ground

9.Tour Texan capital city highlights like Texas State Capitol building , LBJ presidential library , Lady Bird Lake etc 

10.Enjoy mesquite-smoked barbecue or taste Tex-Mex cuisine while visiting local eateries & food trucks throughout various cities
